  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "RA-DENet [65] enhances the representation of different regions through inverse attention, and then eliminates noise through distractor removal.",
    "Net [43] incorporates a text attention mechanism, which utilizes features related to the size and number of polyps to adapt to varying polyp sizes and effectively handle scenarios with multiple polyps.",
    "LDNet [48] extracts global context features from the input image and then updates them iteratively based on the lesion features predicted by the segmentation.",
    "SANet [8] eliminates the impact of colors through a color swap operation, and then filters out background noise from shallow features based on a shallow attention module.",
    "Feature fusion modelsIt is crucial to incorporate multi-scale features to effectively handle variations in object size [81]."
  ],
